fields.name: IN_DONE
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0. For UHCI0, the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data error is detected only in the case that the peripheral is UHCI0 for Rx channel 0. For other peripherals, this raw interrupt is reserved.

fields.name: OUT_DONE
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been transmitted to peripherals for Tx channel 0.

fields.name: OUT_EOF

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY

fields.name: OUT_TOTAL_EOF

1610649604.desc: IO MUX Configure Register for pad XTAL_32K_P

fields.name: MCU_OE
fields.desc: Output enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: output enabled; 0: output disabled.

fields.name: SLP_SEL
fields.desc: Sleep mode selection of this pad. Set to 1 to put the pad in pad mode.

fields.name: MCU_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: internal pull-down enabled; 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: MCU_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: internal pull-up enabled; 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: MCU_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: input enabled; 0: input disabled.

fields.name: FUN_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-down enabled; 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: FUN_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-up enabled; 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: FUN_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad. 1: input enabled; 0: input disabled.

fields.name: FUN_DRV
fields.desc: Select the drive strength of the pad. 0: ~5 mA; 1: ~10mA; 2: ~20mA; 3: ~40mA.

fields.name: MCU_SEL
fields.desc: Select IO MUX function for this signal. 0: Select Function 1; 1: Select Function 2; etc.

fields.name: FILTER_EN
fields.desc: Enable filter for pin input signals. 1: Filter enabled; 2: Filter disabled.

fields.name: REG_DATE
fields.desc: Version control register

fields.name: TIMER_SEL
fields.desc:
This field is used to select one of timers for channel %s.

0: select timer0; 1: select timer1; 2: select timer2; 3: select timer3

fields.name: SIG_OUT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable signal output on channel %s.

fields.name: IDLE_LV
fields.desc: This bit is used to control the output value when channel %s is inactive (when LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s is 0).

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: This bit is used to update LEDC_HPOINT_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_START_CH%s, LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s, LEDC_TIMER_SEL_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_NUM_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_SCALE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_INC_CH%s, and LEDC_OVF_CNT_EN_CH%s fields for channel %s, and will be automatically cleared by hardware.

fields.name: OVF_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the maximum times of overflow minus 1.

The LEDC_OVF_CNT_CH%s_INT interrupt will be triggered when channel %s overflows for (LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH%s + 1) times.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: HPOINT
fields.desc: The output value changes to high when the selected timers has reached the value specified by this register.

fields.name: DUTY
fields.desc:
This register is used to change the output duty by controlling the Lpoint.

The output value turns to low when the selected timers has reached the Lpoint.

fields.name: DUTY_SCALE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the changing step scale of duty on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_CYCLE
fields.desc: The duty will change every LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to control the number of times the duty cycle will be changed.

fields.name: DUTY_INC
fields.desc: This register is used to increase or decrease the duty of output signal on channel %s. 1: Increase; 0: Decrease.

fields.name: DUTY_START
fields.desc: Other configured fields in LEDC_CH%s_CONF1_REG will start to take effect when this bit is set to 1.

fields.name: DUTY_CH0_R
fields.desc: This register stores the current duty of output signal on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_RES
fields.desc: This register is used to control the range of the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: CLK_DIV
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the divisor for the divider in timer %s.

The least significant eight bits represent the fractional part.

fields.name: PAUSE
fields.desc: This bit is used to suspend the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: RST
fields.desc: This bit is used to reset timer %s. The counter will show 0 after reset.

fields.name: TICK_SEL
fields.desc:
This bit is used to select clock for timer %s. When this bit is set to 1 LEDC_APB_CLK_SEL[1:0] should be 1, otherwise the timer clock may be not accurate.

1'h0: SLOW_CLK 1'h1: REF_TICK

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: Set this bit to update LEDC_CLK_DIV_TIMER%s and LEDC_TIMER%s_DUTY_RES.

fields.name: CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the current counter value of timer %s.

fields.name: OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer0 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: FLASH_PER
fields.desc: program erase resume bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_PES
fields.desc: program erase suspend bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase resume command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase resume command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase suspend command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase suspend command is sent.

fields.name: PES_PER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable PES end triggers PER transfer option. If this bit is 0, application should send PER after PES is done.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable Auto-suspending function.

fields.name: PESR_END_MSK
fields.desc: The mask value when check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. If the read status value is status_in[15:0](only status_in[7:0] is valid when only one byte of data is read out, status_in[15:0] is valid when two bytes of data are read out), SUS/SUS1/SUS2 = status_in[15:0]^ SPI_MEM_PESR_END_MSK[15:0].

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_RD_SUS_2B
fields.desc: 1: Read two bytes when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. 0:  Read one byte when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit

fields.name: PER_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the resume status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

fields.name: PES_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the suspend status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

fields.name: SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT
fields.desc: When SPI1 checks SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits fail for SPI_MEM_SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT[6:0] times, it will be treated as check pass.

fields.name: FLASH_PER_COMMAND
fields.desc: Program/Erase resume command.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_COMMAND
fields.desc: Program/Erase suspend command.

fields.name: WAIT_PESR_COMMAND
fields.desc: Flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit read command. The command should be sent when SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit should be checked to insure the suspend or resume status of flash.

fields.name: FLASH_SUS
fields.desc: The status of flash suspend, only used in SPI1.

fields.name: WAIT_PESR_CMD_2B
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[15:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit. 0: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[7:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit.

fields.name: FLASH_HPM_DLY_128
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_RES_DLY_128
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_DP_DLY_128
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_PER_DLY_128
fields.desc: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_DLY_128
fields.desc: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent.

fields.name: SPI0_LOCK_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable SPI0 lock SPI0/1 arbiter option. 0: Disable it.

fields.name: TIMING_CALI

fields.name: EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN

fields.name: USR_ADDR_VALUE

fields.name: FADDR_DUAL

fields.name: FADDR_QUAD

fields.name: FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_OCT
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: HOLD_POL
fields.desc: SPI_HOLD output value when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WP_POL
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RD_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: LSB first 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WR_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: LSB firs 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_clkcnt_N. In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1). In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_clk. So spi_clk frequency is system/(spi_clkdiv_pre+1)/(spi_clkcnt_N+1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKDIV_PRE
fields.desc: In the master mode it is pre-divider of spi_clk.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: In the master mode 1: spi_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_clk is divided from system clock. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DOUTDIN
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable full duplex communication. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: QPI_MODE
fields.desc: Both for master mode and slave mode. 1: spi controller is in QPI mode. 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: OPI_MODE
fields.desc: Just for master mode. 1: spi controller is in OPI mode (all in 8-b-m). 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: TSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of tsck. 0: tsck = spi_ck_i. 1:tsck = !spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of rsck. 0: rsck = !spi_ck_i. 1:rsck = spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: the bit combined with spi_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_DUAL
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_QUAD
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_OCT
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 8 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_CONF_NXT
fields.desc: 1: Enable the DMA CONF phase of next seg-trans operation, which means seg-trans will continue. 0: The seg-trans will end after the current SPI seg-trans or this is not seg-trans mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SIO
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable 3-line half duplex communication mosi and miso signals share the same pin. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO_HIGHPART
fields.desc: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
fields.desc: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI
fields.desc: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO
fields.desc: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bit enable the address phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND
fields.desc: This bit enable the command phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MST_WFULL_ERR_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

fields.name: CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles+1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_setup bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: delay cycles of cs pin by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_hold bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MST_REMPTY_ERR_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: BIT_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to set the length of data.

fields.name: STOP_BIT_NUM

fields.name: SW_RTS
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software rts signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: SW_DTR

fields.name: TXD_BRK

fields.name: IRDA_DPLX

fields.name: IRDA_TX_EN
fields.desc: This is the start enable bit for IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_WCTL
fields.desc: 1'h1: The IrDA transmitter's 11th bit is the same as 10th bit. 1'h0: Set IrDA transmitter's 11th bit to 0.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of  IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_RX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of IrDA receiver.

fields.name: LOOPBACK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart loopback test mode.

fields.name: TX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable flow control function for transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable IrDA protocol.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart receive-FIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart transmit-FIFO.

fields.name: RXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

fields.name: CTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

fields.name: DSR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

fields.name: TXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

fields.name: RTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

fields.name: DTR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: ERR_WR_MASK
fields.desc: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

fields.name: AUTOBAUD_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for detecting baudrate.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_EN
fields.desc: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

fields.name: DIS_RX_DAT_OVF
fields.desc: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

1610612776.name: LOWPULSE
1610612776.desc: Autobaud minimum low pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the value of the minimum duration time of the low level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

1610612780.name: HIGHPULSE
1610612780.desc: Autobaud minimum high pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores  the value of the maxinum duration time for the high level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

fields.name: RXD_EDGE_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the count of rxd edge change. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

fields.name: SW_FLOW_CON_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

fields.name: XONOFF_DEL
fields.desc: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

fields.name: FORCE_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

fields.name: FORCE_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

fields.name: SEND_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: SEND_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

fields.name: XOFF_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xoff char.

fields.name: XOFF_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

fields.name: XON_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xon char.

fields.name: XON_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

fields.name: TX_BRK_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_IDLE_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

fields.name: TX_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

fields.name: RS485_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to choose the rs485 mode.

fields.name: DL0_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: DL1_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: RS485TX_RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver could receive data when the transmitter is transmitting data in rs485 mode.

fields.name: RS485RXBY_TX_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: enable rs485 transmitter to send data when rs485 receiver line is busy.

fields.name: RS485_RX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the receiver's internal data signal.

fields.name: RS485_TX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the transmitter's internal data signal.

fields.name: PRE_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

fields.name: POST_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

fields.name: RX_GAP_TOUT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

fields.name: CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

fields.name: RX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for receive-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

fields.name: TX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for transmit-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

1610612836.name: MEM_TX_STATUS
1610612836.desc: Tx-FIFO write and read offset address.

fields.name: APB_TX_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when software writes Tx-FIFO via APB.

fields.name: TX_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when Tx-FSM reads data via Tx-FIFO_Ctrl.

1610612840.name: MEM_RX_STATUS
1610612840.desc: Rx-FIFO write and read offset address.

fields.name: APB_RX_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in RX-FIFO when software reads data from Rx-FIFO via APB. UART0 is 10'h100. UART1 is 10'h180.

fields.name: RX_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in Rx-FIFO when Rx-FIFO_Ctrl writes Rx-FIFO. UART0 is 10'h100. UART1 is 10'h180.

fields.name: ST_URX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of receiver.

fields.name: ST_UTX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of transmitter.

fields.name: POSEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two positive edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

fields.name: NEGEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two negative edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_B
fields.desc: The  denominator of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_A
fields.desc: The numerator of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_SEL
fields.desc: UART clock source select. 1: 80Mhz, 2: 8Mhz, 3: XTAL.

fields.name: SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Tx/Rx clock.

fields.name: RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx/Rx.

fields.name: TX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Tx clock.

fields.name: RX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Rx clock.

fields.name: TX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx.

fields.name: RX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Rx.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version register.

fields.name: ID
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the uart_id.

fields.name: HIGH_SPEED
fields.desc: This bit used to select synchronize mode. 1: Registers are auto synchronized into UART Core clock and UART core should be keep the same with APB clock. 0: After configure registers, software needs to write 1 to UART_REG_UPDATE to synchronize registers.

fields.name: REG_UPDATE
fields.desc: Software write 1 would synchronize registers into UART Core clock domain and would be cleared by hardware after synchronization is done.

fields.name: LINESIZE
fields.desc: This bit stores the line size parameter. 0: 16Byte, 1: 32Byte.

fields.name: DESTINATION
fields.desc: This bit stores the destination. 0: flash(default). 1: reserved.

fields.name: PHYSICAL_ADDRESS
fields.desc: Those bits stores the physical address. If linesize is 16-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 16 bytes. If linesize is 32-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 32 bytes.

fields.name: TRIGGER
fields.desc: Set this bit to start manual encryption calculation

fields.name: RELEASE
fields.desc: Set this bit to release the manual encrypted result, after that the result will be visible to spi

fields.name: DESTROY
fields.desc: Set this bit to destroy XTS-AES result.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: Those bits shows XTS-AES status. 0=IDLE, 1=WORK, 2=RELEASE, 3=USE. IDLE means that XTS-AES is idle. WORK means that XTS-AES is busy with calculation. RELEASE means the encrypted result is generated but not visible to mspi. USE means that the encrypted result is visible to mspi.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Those bits stores the version information of XTS-AES.
